Privacy Policy for Revlo

Last Updated: 25 October 2024

Wincosystems (“we,” “us,” or “our”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect from users (“you” or “your”) of our telematics app, how we use and protect that information, and your rights regarding your data.

1. Information We Collect

	•	Personal Information: We may collect identifiable information, such as your name, email address, and phone number, to create and manage your account.
	•	Driving and Location Data: With your permission, we collect GPS data, driving behavior, and location-based information to analyze and improve your driving safety.
	•	Vehicle Information: We collect information about your vehicle, such as make, model, and year, to ensure accurate tracking and insights.
	•	Device Information: We collect information from your device, including device ID, operating system, and network information, to support app functionality and improve performance.

2. How We Use Your Information

	•	Road Safety and Driving Insights: We use collected data to provide insights into driving behavior, suggest safety improvements, and promote safer driving habits.
	•	Feature Improvement and Development: We analyze usage patterns to enhance app functionality and improve user experience.
	•	Communication: We may use your contact information to send you important updates, notifications, and support communications.
	•	Compliance and Legal Purposes: We may disclose data as required by law or in response to legal requests to protect our rights or comply with legal obligations.

3. Data Sharing and Disclosure

	•	With Service Providers: We share data with third-party service providers who assist us in operating and maintaining the app, such as hosting and analytics services.
	•	Business Transfers: If Wincosystems undergoes a business transaction, such as a merger or acquisition, your information may be transferred to the successor organization.
	•	Legal Requirements: We may disclose information if required to comply with legal obligations or to protect the rights, safety, and property of our company, users, or others.

4. Data Security

	•	We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no transmission over the internet is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Data Retention

	•	We retain your data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy or as required by law. When data is no longer needed, we will delete or anonymize it securely.

6. Your Rights and Choices

	•	Access and Correction: You can access, correct, or update your personal information within the app settings or by contacting us.
	•	Data Deletion: You may request the deletion of your data at any time. Some data may need to be retained for legal or security reasons.
	•	Opt-Out of Location Tracking: You can disable location tracking through your device settings. However, this may limit the app’s functionality.

7. Children’s Privacy

	•	Our app is not intended for use by children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such data, please contact us to delete it.

8. Changes to this Privacy Policy

	•	We may update this policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of significant updates within the app or via email.

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:

Wincosystems,
luke@wincosystems.com
